# Hindsight memory — {{BANK_ID}}

This project uses Hindsight bank `{{BANK_ID}}` (see `.mcp.json`).
Auto-recall and auto-retain are enabled via `.claude/settings.local.json`.

## What happens automatically

- **Before each user prompt** the `recall.js` hook searches this bank for
  relevant memories and silently appends them to the message. Claude sees
  them, the user does not.
- **After each response** the `retain.js` hook saves the transcript once
  every N turns.
- **On session end** `session-end.js` forces a final retain.

So **don't call `memory_recall` and `memory_retain` reflexively** — it's
already happening. Manual calls are only for the special cases below.

