## When to invoke a tool by hand

- `memory_recall(query)` — only if the auto-hook didn't fire (very short
  prompt, or session just started). Usually not needed.
- `memory_retain(content)` — when the user explicitly says "remember X",
  or when you arrive at a **non-obvious decision / lesson** that auto-retain
  could dilute in the transcript stream.
- `memory_reflect(query)` — when the user wants a **synthesis** over a
  topic, not raw facts. E.g. "give me the big picture on auth", "what
  open tech debt do we have?".
- `mental_model_get(id)` — when the question matches one of the mental
  models above. Reading the page gives coherent synthesis instead of a
  spray of raw facts.
- `document_ingest_file(path)` — when we've produced a significant
  artifact (PRD, RFC, ADR, postmortem) and want it semantically
  searchable, not just findable by name with `Read`.

## What NOT to store in this bank

- Contents of PRD/RFC/ADR — they live in `forge/` and are read via `Read`
- Global conventions — those belong in `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`
- Git history — `git log` has it
- `.mcp.json` config or env vars
- Secrets, tokens, credentials

## Diagnostics for this bank

```
memory_status            # health + statistics
memory_get_current_bank  # confirm bank_id
mental_model_list        # list living pages
```

